JOHANNESBURG, November 8 – The Telkom Knockout semifinal fixtures venues, dates and kick-off times were confirmed by the Premier Soccer League on Thursday.
The semifinals will be played on the weekend of 24-25 November 2018.
The first semifinal will be between Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates at Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban on Saturday, 24 November (15h00).
The second fixture will be played on Sunday, 25 November at Peter Mokaba Stadium between Baroka FC and Bidvest Wits  (15h00).
For the first semifinal at Moses Mabhida (Kaizer Chiefs vs Orlando Pirates), tickets will be selling at R80. The second semifinal (Baroka FC vs Bidvest Wits will be selling at R40 at Peter Mokaba. (ANA)